If the subject name contains "Pre-AP," it is classified as Pre-AP. If the subject name includes "AP" or "IB," it is labeled as an "AP/IB subject." Otherwise, it is considered a regular school course.
For Pre-AP or AP/IB subjects, the credit value is constant at 1. However, for regular subjects, there are typically three credit conditions (1, 0.25, 0.5), varying by school policy. Generally, subjects like English, science, and math carry a full credit (1). However, Arabic subjects may have different credit values, with the school's Arabic course generally being worth 1 credit, while other Arabic subjects depend on individual school policies. It's advisable to consult your teacher for clarification.
